verdict_level: Phase-position semantics confirmed; material-level identity NOT supported
summary: Rare/tail MIDDLEs show strong phase-position structuring (zone-exclusivity, section clustering, line-final rarity) but discrimination tests consistently favor operational variants over material identifiers. The semantic ceiling holds with a refinement: phase-position semantics is more structured than previously appreciated.

detail.test_10: C619 holds within phases — unique MIDDLEs do NOT show different transition profiles. Strongly favors operational.
detail.test_11: Phase-exclusivity survives Mann-Whitney (p=0.009) but NOT permutation baseline (p=0.144). Partially favors material, partially null.
detail.test_12: Finish-exclusive MIDDLEs are NOT enriched for FL characters (p=0.224). Rules out FL state-marking as explanation. Favors material.
detail.test_13: Cross-folio tail sharing weakly correlates with PP similarity (rho=0.123). Below r>0.2 threshold. Neutral-to-operational.
detail.test_14: 89.4% of zone-exclusive rare MIDDLEs are distance-1 from common MIDDLEs. They are compositional elaborations, not independent identifiers. Strongly favors operational.

A_operational_phase_specificity.interpretation: Rare MIDDLEs are operational variants deployed in specific procedural phases, not material identifiers

B_fl_state_index.interpretation: FL state marking does NOT explain zone-exclusive vocabulary

C_compositional_morphology_artifact.evidence: Test 14 — 89.4% distance-1, 97.9% contain a common atom
C_compositional_morphology_artifact.interpretation: Zone-exclusive tails ARE compositional variants, but their phase-restriction is real, not artifactual

D_folio_identity_vocabulary.evidence: Tests 4, 7 — BIO folios don't cluster, atom sharing weak
D_folio_identity_vocabulary.interpretation: Folio-specific vocabulary is not organized by material identity

findings_for_constraint_system.finding: Rare MIDDLEs are significantly more zone-exclusive than common MIDDLEs
Rare MIDDLEs cluster by manuscript section
Line-final position enriched for rare MIDDLEs (but explained by suffix morphology)
findings_for_constraint_system.evidence: OR=1.83, p<1e-27, but suffix confound confirmed

findings_for_constraint_system.finding: Sections maintain distinct tail vocabulary (42-66% section-exclusive)
Zone-exclusive rare MIDDLEs are compositional elaborations (89.4% distance-1)
findings_for_constraint_system.evidence: Mean edit distance 1.11, 97.9% contain a common atom
findings_for_constraint_system.candidate_constraint: C9XX: Zone-exclusive MIDDLEs are compositional variants

findings_for_constraint_system.finding: C619 (unique MIDDLE behavioral equivalence) holds within procedural phases
findings_for_constraint_system.evidence: JSD=0.01 overall, no zone significant after Bonferroni

semantic_ceiling_impact.revised_position: C120 STANDS with refinement: tail MIDDLEs show phase-position specificity but are compositional variants of common operational MIDDLEs, not independent material identifiers
semantic_ceiling_impact.key_nuance: The fact that finish-exclusive vocabulary is NOT FL-state markers (Test 12) means phase-exclusivity has a procedural explanation beyond state-indexing, but the explanation remains operational (different operational variants for different procedural phases) rather than referential (different materials)
semantic_ceiling_impact.practical_implication: Material encoding, if present, does NOT live in MIDDLE morphology. It would need to come from a source outside the compositional token structure — possibly from context (which MIDDLEs appear together), from the illustrations, or from external knowledge

notes: Verdict criteria: STRONG (10+/14 significant, discrimination favors material), MODERATE (7-9/14, mixed discrimination), WEAK (4-6/14, discrimination favors operational), NULL (<4/14). Score: 4 supported + 3 partial = 4-7 depending on counting. Discrimination tests: 3 operational, 1 material, 1 neutral. Net: WEAK with important structural findings.
